# 3️⃣ `.gitignore` (Very Aggressive & Predictive)

This ignores:
- Compiled files
- Editors
- OS junk
- Python envs
- Node stuff
- Java / C / C++ / Rust / Go / etc.
- Future languages
- Random trash files

Create a file named **`.gitignore`**:

```gitignore
# ================================
# OS FILES
# ================================
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ================================
# EDITORS & IDEs
# ================================
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*.bak
*.tmp
*.log
*.orig

# ================================
# C / C++
# ================================
*.o
*.out
*.obj
*.exe
*.a
*.so
*.dll

# ================================
# Python
# ================================
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.venv/
venv/
env/
pip-wheel-metadata/
.pytest_cache/

# ================================
# Node / JavaScript / TypeScript
# ================================
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-lock.yaml
dist/
build/

# ================================
# Web / Frontend
# ================================
.cache/
.parcel-cache/

# ================================
# Java
# ================================
*.class
*.jar
*.war
*.ear
hs_err_pid*

# ================================
# Go
# ================================
*.exe~
*.test
*.prof

# ================================
# Rust
# ================================
target/

# ================================
# C#
# ================================
bin/
obj/

# ================================
# PHP
# ================================
vendor/

# ================================
# Databases
# ================================
*.sqlite
*.db

# ================================
# Archives
# ================================
*.zip
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.rar
*.7z

# ================================
# ENV & SECRETS
# ================================
.env
.env.*
*.key
*.pem

# ================================
# Misc / Junk
# ================================
*.tmp
*.cache
*.crash
*.lock
